alizava.caption: After my morning swim in the lake at the campsite, made this point my first stop. I found it in a wheat field half a kilometer from a gravel road. There was a path through the wheat on the way to the exact point. Felt a connection with my fellow visitors!
alizava.name: Alizava

andelka.caption: Crossed from Poland into Czechia on a dirt road, and continued about a kilometer to the village of Andělka. There’s a little park with a bench, an explanation sign and a rock at the exact point. Continued on to visit the Turów Coal Mine.
andelka.name: Andělka

arnstein.caption: This point has a spherical stone monument right off a road, surrounded by an arc of benches and a cluster of trees. Technically it’s a diversion, as the exact point is 250 meters away in a planted field.
arnstein.name: Arnstein

avizonys.caption: After passing through Kernavė, found this point near the road in a plowed field. The owner was there mowing his lawn. Didn’t feel like trying to explain CPs in Lithuanian or getting my shoes muddy, so settled for 150m. Continued on to my second Struve point.
avizonys.name: Avižonys

bergen.caption: This point is in some woods about 400 meters from a suburban cul-de-sac. Used the compass to walk through the trees and found the exact spot. Saw some deer. 🦌 Continued to Grand & Union in Palisades Park and King Spa.
bergen.name: Bergen

bievre.caption: This point is 15m from the N385 road, which is so close that driving by almost counts as a precise visit. It’s about 300 meters from the Namur / Luxembourg provincial border, and also close to the Givet salient.
bievre.name: Bièvre

blairstown.caption: this point is deep in the woods about 1.5 km from the highway that leads to the Delaware Water Gap. Near Mount Pleasant, NJ and Portland, PA.
blairstown.name: Blairstown

blankenbach.caption: Parked in a rest area and walked across a planted field to find this spot, which had a sign claiming that I was now standing the geographical center of Germany. Not sure how they reckon but yes I felt very centered at that moment.
blankenbach.name: Blankenbach

cape-charles.caption: This point is in the mouth of the Chesapeake Bay. After visiting the town of Cape Charles, passed within 7 km while crossing the Chesapeake Bay Bridge-Tunnel.
cape-charles.name: Cape Charles

cape-cod.caption: Drove to the very end of Cape Cod, as one does, and found the end of US Route 6 in Provincetown. The point is 4 km off the coast from Highland Lighthouse.
cape-cod.name: Cape Cod

cape-may.caption: This point is 3 km off the shore of Cape May, the southern point of New Jersey. Continued on the ferry to Lewes in Delaware.
cape-may.name: Cape May

centreville.caption: Found this point on the way from Dover to Annapolis. Parked by side of a country road and walked along the side of a corn field. Found a worn path through the grass to the exact point. Not the first geography nerd here!
centreville.name: Centreville

cologne.caption: The GPS made it look like this point would be easy to visit, but when I got there at night I found that the access road was blocked about 1 km away. It’s actually right on a railway embankment, so if I want to try again I’ll take the S-Bahn.
cologne.name: Cologne

concord.caption: This point is fifty meters inside Naval Weapons Station Seal Beach, just off a parking lot on Willow Pass Road. I was content to pass within 1 km on the BART Yellow Line on the way to Pittsburg/Bay Point station.
concord.name: Concord

coutts-ab.caption: Crossed into Canada on the way to Calgary about 3 km from this point, which is technically about 200 meters north of the border.
coutts-ab.name: Coutts, AB

dendermonde.caption: This point is in a planted field just off a residential street and across a railroad track. Drove down the nearest dirt path, but it was pouring rain and very muddy so I was content to get within 200m by car.
dendermonde.name: Dendermonde

didziosios-lapes.caption: My first time swimming to a confluence point! Hiked through some farmland to this gorgeous lake surrounded by reeds. Found a little spot to leave my clothes and swam out to the exact point. Now where were those clothes?
didziosios-lapes.name: Didžiosios Lapės

drums.caption: Parked at the foot of an old railway embankment with a bridge that’s no longer there. Walked along the road and found the exact point in front of a house with an angry dog. Continued on to Scranton and discovered locomotive nirvana at 🚂 Steamtown!
drums.name: Drums

druskininkai.caption: Fresh from visiting the town’s famous Soviet spa, proceeded to this nearby sports complex. The hotel for athletes was built with the corner of the building at the exact confluence point. Rock on, geography nerd architect!
druskininkai.name: Druskininkai

east-berlin.caption: This point is in some woods about 50m from the Baltimore Pike. The area is a gold mine for twin cities  like Hanover, New Oxford, Dover… and of course East Berlin.
east-berlin.name: East Berlin

enscherange.caption: Considering this is Luxembourg’s only confluence point, they’ve done some nice aménagement with a garden, hedges, a bench, an explanatory sign, and a sundial at the exact point.
enscherange.name: Enscherange

eugene.caption: Passed within 500m of this point while driving up Interstate 5 towards Portland.
eugene.name: Eugene

exeter.caption: This point is deep in a marsh. Closest I could get was 1 km away at the entrance to an industrial area. Exeter is famous for its prestigious boarding school, as exemplified by this cheeky street sign.
exeter.name: Exeter

fletching.caption: Visited Sheffield Park station on the Bluebell Railway, and got to see a working steam engine shuttling back and forth. Skipped the excursion ride, which was expensive and required advance booking. The exact point was in a muddy field half a kilometer away.
fletching.name: Fletching

froxfield.caption: Hired a car for the day to bag two CPs. Found this one along a stereotypical country lane with hedge rows on both sides. Knocked at the door of the manor but found nobody home. Walked to the exact point on the driveway outside a barn.
froxfield.name: Froxfield

gangelt.caption: This was a very easy point to visit, and I found the exact point in a field of grass by a farmhouse near a village.
gangelt.name: Gangelt

gap.caption: Drove to this point in Amish country, east of Lancaster. Saw lots of horses and buggies. Found this point in the backyard of a house, about 250m from the road.
gap.name: Gap

gattendorf.caption: Passed by after visiting the 🇦🇹 🇭🇺 🇸🇰 tripoint which is also the eastern point of Austria. Found the exact point in a planted field about 200 meters from the road.
gattendorf.name: Gattendorf

gemunden.caption: This point involved a pleasant walk through a canopy of trees, and the exact point was easy to find. I found a hunting tower and climbed up to the top.
gemunden.name: Gemünden

golden-beach.caption: Ditto above, 15 km off the coast.
golden-beach.name: Golden Beach

grand-canyon.caption: This point is just over the edge of the Grand Canyon. Passed within 500m while driving along the South Rim. Went for a helicopter ride to see the canyon up close!
grand-canyon.name: Grand Canyon

grand-island.caption: After visiting Niagara Falls, went looking for this point on Grand Island. Parked on the road and approached from the south, passing through the backyard of some houses. Followed a network of trails to the exact point.
grand-island.name: Grand Island

greenwich-observatory.caption: Turns out the actual Prime Meridian is about 40 meters east of the ceremonial line marked at the observatory.
greenwich-observatory.name: Greenwich Observatory

gulbene.caption: Went hunting for this point on my way from Jēkabpils back to Lithuania. The GPS took me up a windy track into the hills, and I parked by a rustic cabin. Walked around a field, through a bog, along a culvert, and stumbled to the bloody exact point deep in some thick woods. Was almost eaten alive by mosquitoes. Met a local on the way out.
gulbene.name: Gulbene

hoquiam.caption: On our tour of the Olympic Peninsula in an American muscle car, turned off Highway 101 at Aberdeen and drove along the shore of Grays Harbor. Stopped 50m from the point, just off the driveway of a house where it looks like they have lots of guns.
hoquiam.name: Hoquiam

istanbul.caption: This point is in the Sea of Marmara, just south of the mouth of the Bosporous and about 2 km southeast of the Hagia Sophia. Next time I can take the new Marmaray Tunnel to get even closer!
istanbul.name: Istanbul

josefsthal.caption: Went looking for this point around the corner from the northern point of Austria. Hiked through the woods in the rain for about an hour, then followed the border with Czechia just along the shore of Staňkovský rybník. Found a stone marker at the exact point. Getting out was much easier than getting in.
josefsthal.name: Josefsthal

jupiter.caption: Passed nearby this point 10 km off the Florida coast on the Brightline train from Orlando to Miami. Looks like a 🚄 TGV, it’s actualy a diesel. Many passengers were taking a train for the first time.
jupiter.name: Jupiter

kasese.caption: The road through the Queen Elizabeth National Park crosses the Equator just 75m from the confluence point. Road sign warns of 🦌 gazelles, actually saw an 🐘 elephant.
kasese.name: Kasese

kazliski.caption: After leaving Daugavpils, easily found the exact point in a beautiful meadow half a kilometer from the road.
kazliski.name: Kazliški

kourim.caption: Parked on a country road and walked a hundred meters along the side of a corn field. What’s this? Someone cleared a square around the exact point and put a sign! Celebrated by having some corn in the rain. Clearly Czechia is the center of Europe.
kourim.name: Kouřim

kreuztal.caption: This one looked like it was going to be easy, but getting to the exact point involved climbing over a gate and bushwhacking through a field of weeds. Was looking forward to the next point in Cologne, which I thought would be easier…
kreuztal.name: Kreuztal

krov-bausendorf.caption: This point was super easy to visit, with parking and a dirt path straight to the exact point only fifty meters off the road.
krov-bausendorf.name: Kröv-Bausendorf

kuldiga.caption: Kuldīga is a world heritage site known for the Venta Rapid. This point is deep in the forest and it was after dark, so I passed within 2 km and visited the waterfall instead.
kuldiga.name: Kuldīga

lantriac.caption: Drove to the town of Lantriac to the southeast of Le Puy-en-Velay for my first intentional confluence point visit! Parked outside a house 30m from the point in the backyard. Here’s a pic of the GPS in the BMW that shows I was 1″ away.
lantriac.name: Lantriac

lawrenceville-pa.caption: Parked the car 200 meters from the road, and found the exact point in a lovely grass field about 100 meters south of the state line. Not to be confused with the CP in Lawrenceville, GA!
lawrenceville-pa.name: Lawrenceville, PA

le-roy.caption: Found the exact point on the pavement of Bergen Road, about halfway between the town of Le Roy and Interstate 90. Saw another car pull up and do a U-turn at the point… perhaps the only time I’ve encountered another CP hunter in the wild.
le-roy.name: Le Roy

leskovac.caption: Passed within 2 km of this point while driving on the A1 from Skopje to Belgrade.
leskovac.name: Leskovac

lewisburg.caption: Parked at the end of the driveway of this lovely country home with willow trees. The exact point is literally at their front door. Went to a pub in Lewisburg with paintings of 🐮 cows.
lewisburg.name: Lewisburg

mainhausen.caption: This point is 40m off the A3 Autobahn, so I counted that as close enough.
mainhausen.name: Mainhausen

malibu.caption: This point is 7 km off the Pacific Coast Highway in Malibu. Stopped to visit Christina after driving through Death Valley.
malibu.name: Malibu

mcconnellsburg.caption: Parked at the bottom of the driveway and walked up to the house. Found the owner and asked to visit his field. He wasn’t familiar with CPs, so I explained “there’s these nerds on the internet…” He loved the idea, said I was the first visitor to ask his permission, and happily showed me how to get to the exact spot. Met three very friendly horses.
mcconnellsburg.name: McConnellsburg

medzula.caption: After visiting two Struve points, tried to get to this point which is in a lake. I was prepared to swim for it, but after driving to the end of driveway found that it was on private property. Got within 300m.
medzula.name: Mēdzula

meemaste.caption: After a long day in which I survived a short drive through Russia, I wanted to make it to Tartu. This point is located on an overgrown logging road. It was pitch black and pouring rain, and the GPS got me within 250m on a dirt road.
meemaste.name: Meemaste

montauk.caption: Took the LIRR to Montauk just to go to the end. Passed this point which is about 1 km offshore. Skated to Montauk Point Light and the eastern point of New York State.
montauk.name: Montauk

mukvyatitsa.caption: Passed within 15 km of this point while driving along the border with Belarus.
mukvyatitsa.name: Mukvyatitsa

nabusanke.caption: We stayed in local style hotel for truckers right on the equator, about 5 km from the confluence point. Basically an orange concrete box, but it came with good food and cost about $7. Road was lined with posters for Museveni every hundred meters.
nabusanke.name: Nabusanke

nakuru.caption: Crossed the equator about 4 km from the confluence point, on the way to Lake Bogoria. Road was diabolical but the journey was worth it as the lake has about a third of the world's 🦩 flamingos, many of them dead.
nakuru.name: Nakuru

nanyuki.caption: Crossed the equator here about 7 km east of the confluence point. This is one of the most touristy places to visit the equator in Kenya, so you have to stop the car, take your picture and keep going before the people selling trinkets or pushing scams get you.
nanyuki.name: Nanyuki

new-smyrna.caption: This point is 2 km deep in a swamp, so Ragh and I went to Walmart across the road instead for some classy box wine 🍷 and Florida 😎 fridge magnets. Met someone with a very smart dog. Also my first time at 🦫 Buc-ee’s, a life-changing experience.
new-smyrna.name: New Smyrna

oestrich-winkel.caption: Stopped for a latte at a cutesy vintage German cafe, where they don’t take credit cards but didn’t bat an eyelash when I paid with a €100 bill. This point is in the side yard of a house, 10m from the street. We ate some grapes growing nearby.
oestrich-winkel.name: Oestrich-Winkel

paris-va.caption: After visiting Paris, drove up Route 17 and turned off into the hills. The road turned to gravel, and then I got to a gate with a big No Trespassing sign 1 km from the point. People here have guns. Turned around just as a mail truck was doing the same.
paris-va.name: Paris, VA

phelps.caption: Parked by the side of the road and walked about 200 meters along the edge of a planted field. Found the exact point inside a thinly forested area. Enjoyed the fall colors while walking through the leaves.
phelps.name: Phelps

point-pleasant.caption: As I was exploring the Jersey Shore, passed by this point about 5 km off the barrier island. Continued on to Atlantic City, where I visited every street on the Monopoly board.
point-pleasant.name: Point Pleasant

point-reyes.caption: This point should be in the Pacific Ocean off the coast of California, but it just happens to be on the Point Reyes peninsula. Hiked to within 300m of the point.
point-reyes.name: Point Reyes

prachatice.caption: After Nová Pec, crossed into Czechia and went to the village of Prachatice. In the woods just off a road on the south side of town there's a stone marker and a sculpture at the exact point. Czechs love their marked points! Continued on to Zvikov Castle.
prachatice.name: Prachatice

prachomety.caption: Passed by this point on the way from Plzeň to Mariánské Lázně. Parked in the villiage of Branišov and hiked about a kilometer. Found a sign at the exact point, on a hillside with harvested trees. Celebrated by going for a swim in a lake nearby with a ruined castle.
prachomety.name: Prachomety

pruseliai.caption: Found this point right off the dam of an artificial lake. Scrambled down the embankment through some nettles, and got to within 15m of the point which was deep in a thicket. Celebrated by going for a swim in the lake afterwards.
pruseliai.name: Prūseliai

putinci.caption: Passed within 700m of this point while taking the train from Ljubljana via Zagreb to Belgrade.
putinci.name: Putinci

qara.caption: Passed by this point 500m from the road driving through the Sahara Desert from Marsa Matrouh to Siwa Oasis. Just endless sky, sand and road. They put a camel warning sign every kilometer to break the monotony.
qara.name: Qāra

ramma.caption: I was on the way between two Struve points and the northern point of Estonia. The exact point was easy to get to, in a fallow field about a hundred meters from a gravel road.
ramma.name: Ramma

riga.caption: Picked up the rental car and drove directly to this point between Riga and Jūrmala. Parked on a forest road and hiked through a magical forest for half a kilometer. This one has a waypost sign at the exact point!
riga.name: Riga

risti.caption: Spent the day exploring Tallinn, 28 years after my first visit. Hotels were crazy expensive so I decided to continue towards the western point of Estonia. Drove by on National Road 9 within 1.5 km of the point, which was deep in the woods.
risti.name: Risti

riverton.caption: This point in some thick woods 100m from the road. Not to be confused with Riverton Country Club.
riverton.name: Riverton

riverton-country-club.caption: This point is located in a golf course just outside Philadelphia. Drove through a residential area to get to a spot along the fence 200m from the point. There is a stone marker in the ground, the only marked point in the states that I've been to.
riverton-country-club.name: Riverton Country Club

roscoe.caption: Drove up into the Catskills, enjoying the fall foliage. Parked 400m from the point, which is in the woods on private property. Found the historic town of Roscoe to be quite scenic, with a train museum. Turns out Algoe, NY is not a real place.
roscoe.name: Roscoe

sahuarita.caption: This point is on the edge of the reclamation pond of an old copper mine. Passed within 750m while driving down Interstate 19 from Tucson to Nogales, as part of a road trip to Mexico in my first car.
sahuarita.name: Sahuarita

salem-or.caption: Passed within 50m of this point which is literally on an entrance ramp of Interstate 5.
salem-or.name: Salem, OR

scheßlitz.caption: This point was easy to get to, and involved walking a few hundred meters across a planted field. Found the exact point just inside a cluster of trees.
scheßlitz.name: Scheßlitz

seaside.caption: Passed by this point 5 km off the coast while driving up towards Astoria and Cape Disappointment, which wasn’t disappointing at all.
seaside.name: Seaside

silver-spring.caption: Celebrated completing the Boundary Stones by visiting this point in Silver Spring, halfway between the city line and the Beltway. The exact point is located at the corner of an apartment building at 8662 Piney Branch Road, next to Long Branch Pool.
silver-spring.name: Silver Spring

somerset.caption: Parked on a country road and walked to the exact point, in a field full of wildflowers just twenty meters off the road. There were paths in the grass from other visitors. Locals asked, “are you from out of state?” Continued to Berlin for a life-changing latte.
somerset.name: Somerset

sovyetsk.caption: Passed within 5 km of this point while driving along the border of Kaliningrad Oblast, an exclave of Russia.
sovyetsk.name: Sovyetsk

square-ambiorix.caption: Not technically a CP but interesting nonetheless as its coordinates are 50°50′50″. In a hedge in a beautiful square in Brussels, surrounded by fountains and art deco buildings.
square-ambiorix.name: Square Ambiorix

staden.caption: This point is in the backyard of a farmhouse in the Flemish countryside. They put a sign on the house that says, “You found it!” so people won’t bother them about visiting their yard. So got to 15m, close enough. Continued on to Thermen R in Roeselare.
staden.name: Staden

talcis.caption: Right next to the northern point of Latvia, this point is within a kilometer of the Estonian border. Looked like it would be possible to access via some logging roads, but they were overgrown and impassable. Settled for 500m away.
talcis.name: Talcis

ulster.caption: What could possibly top operating a streetcar at the Trolley Museum of New York? Visiting this confluence point, in a marsh about 50m from the road, close to the New York State Thruway.
ulster.name: Ulster

vestal.caption: Parked at a smoke shop on the Pennsylvania state line, and walked north along the road about a hundred meters. Snuck between some houses in total darkness and found the exact point in the woods just up the hill.
vestal.name: Vestal

video-id=myvideo-controls-preload=none-p.name: <video id="myVideo" controls preload="none" poster="https://images.andrewzc.net/confluence/kreuztal3.jpg" width="1240" height="520" style="margin: 15px 0px -15px 0px"><source src="https://images.andrewzc.net/confluence/kreuztal-1080.mp4" type="video/mp4"></video>

vilksala.caption: This point is in the woods 250m off the A10. Next stop, Kuldīga.
vilksala.name: Vilksala

waverly.caption: After driving down the Atlantic coast to Norfolk, passed by this point on the way up to Petersburg and Richmond. The point is deep in the woods and it was after dark, so took a little detour from the main road to pass within 500m.
waverly.name: Waverly

west-bridgewater.caption: Found the exact point literally on the pavement in a suburban housing development. Super easy!
west-bridgewater.name: West Bridgewater

willow-grove.caption: Drove into Canada for my first international CP in North America! Walked through some woods, under some high voltage power lines, and found the exact point in a harvested hay field. Visited the nearby Six Nations of the Grand River reservation.
willow-grove.name: Willow Grove

woodstock.caption: The exact point is literally in front of the garage door of a suburban house. Continued on to the CR-MA-RI tripoint!
woodstock.name: Woodstock

wunsiedel.caption: Started by hiking through the Luisenburg Felsenlabyrinth, a formation of massive boulders. Got lost bushwacking through the woods. As I was locating the exact point a passing hiker asked if I needed help, and when I explained he said, “Ach so, der Konfluenzpunkt!” Went for a little dip in a spring afterwards.
wunsiedel.name: Wunsiedel

zalavas.caption: Bloody Siri sent me down all these random dirt roads to the wrong point. Actual point was 750m deep in the mosquito infested woods. Continued on for more Belarus border adventures.
zalavas.name: Zalavas

zichem.caption: When I tried to access this point Belgium had just received an unsual amount of rain, and the whole area was flooded. Only got to within 400m because I was blocked by flood waters. The point is only 150 meters from a train line, so maybe one day I’ll try again.
zichem.name: Zichem
